properties.headline: Gale Warning issued January 4 at 4:35AM EST until January 5 at 10:00AM EST by NWS Melbourne FL
properties.description:
...GALE WARNING NOW IN EFFECT FROM 7 PM THIS EVENING TO 10 AM
SUNDAY...

* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, northwest winds 20 to 30 kt with
gusts up to 40 kt and seas 8 to 13 feet expected. For the Small
Craft Advisory, southwest winds 15 to 25 kt with gusts up to 30
kt. Seas up to 8 feet.

* WHERE...Flagler Beach to Volusia-Brevard County Line 20-60 nm,
Volusia-Brevard County Line to Sebastian Inlet 20-60 nm and
Sebastian Inlet to Jupiter Inlet 20-60 nm.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, from 7 PM this evening to 10 AM
Sunday. For the Small Craft Advisory, until 7 PM this evening.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for gale conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 7 PM THIS EVENING
